5000|$|Historically, {{four of the}} <b>Bantustans</b> (or [...] "Black homelands") of South Africa {{were granted}} nominal independence, unrecognized internationally, by the Nationalist {{government}} from 1976 until their reabsorption in 1994. Others remained under government rule from 1948 to 1994. Being heavily partitioned, various parts of these <b>Bantustans</b> were true enclaves.|$|R
