50|$|The Bantu Investment Corporation Act, Act No 34 of 1959, formed {{part of the}} {{apartheid}} system of racial segregation in South Africa. In combination with the Bantu Homelands Development Act of 1965, it allowed the South African government to capitalize on entrepreneurs operating in the <b>Bantustans.</b> It created a Development Corporation {{in each of the}} <b>Bantustans.</b>|$|R
